&lt;h2 id="garden">Garden&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>Rural Villa in Ferpicloz&lt;/p>
&lt;h3 id="keywords">Keywords&lt;/h3>
&lt;p>archaeological garden \&lt;/p>
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>&lt;a href="http://vocab.getty.edu/page/aat/300004145">porticoes&lt;/a>&lt;/li>
&lt;li>&lt;a href="http://vocab.getty.edu/page/aat/300005518">villae rusticae&lt;/a>&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;h3 id="garden-description">Garden Description&lt;/h3>
&lt;p>The house of this &lt;em>villa rustica&lt;/em> was of the winged corridor type (A in Fig. 1) with a porticoed facade (Fig. 1). Attached to the eastern end of the house, measuring 37 x 46 meters, was a wall running east-west which has been interpreted as the protective wall of a garden (G in Fig. 1).&lt;/p>
